Description: Percentage turn of the steering wheel (0 represents straight/ 360 is one rotation/ counter clockwise is positive)
Is the driver interacting with the steering wheel (True = yes/ False = no)
Door or hood open (True = Door or Hood open/ False = Door and Hood closed)
airbag is deployed (True = Airbag deployed/ False = Airbag not deployed)
driver seatbelt is unbuckled (True = unbuckled/ False = buckled)
Cruise control resume button press (True = Button pressed/ False = Button not pressed)
Cruise control cancel button press (True = Button pressed/ False = Button not pressed)
Cruise control accelerate button press (True = Button pressed/ False = Button not pressed)
Cruise control decelerate button press (True = Button pressed/ False = Button not pressed)
Cruise control on/off button press (True = Button pressed/ False = Button not pressed)
Driver Input to Turn Signal (TURN_SIGNAL_OFF/ TURN_SIGNAL_RIGHT/ TURN_SIGNAL_LEFT)
Driver Input to Front Wipers (Off = FRONT_WIPER_OFF)
Acceleration pedal status (True = Engaged/ False = Disengaged)
Does the vehicle accept acceleration pedal inputs from the driver (True = Ignore driver inputs/ False = Accept driver inputs)
Is the driver interacting with the acceleration pedal (True = Yes/ False = No)
Brake pedal status (True = Engaged/ False = Disengaged)
Is the driver interacting with the brake pedal (True = Yes/ False = No)
Drive by wire status (True = Ready/ False = Not Ready)
